	"name": "Edict of the Keeper",
	"type": "feature",
	"img": "icons/magic/fire/dagger-rune-enchant-orange.webp",
	"system": {
		"description": "<p>You empower an object or structure with the presence of your flame. As an action, touch an unattended object (such as a gate, weapon, banner, or piece of armor) and bind it with your flame. For the next 8 hours, the object radiates warmth and cannot be extinguished or corrupted by magic. If the object is part of a building or defensive structure, it gains resistance to fire and cold damage. Any creature that attempts to steal or desecrate the object takes 2d6 fire damage.</p>",
